BLOCK 6: POWER BI TOOL DESCRIPTION
Paste into: Tools > Run a query against a dataset > Description field
================================================================

Queries live data from the Halliburton Sites and Costs Summary Power BI semantic model. Use this tool whenever the user asks about site counts, NBV, ROU, expired contracts, billing, costs, facilities, contracts, PSL coverage, or risk indicators.

Key measures (use exact names in DAX):
[Count_Expired_Contract], [Count_Expired_Contract_No_SR], [Count_ActContr_on_TermSite], [Count_ActLeasedSite_No_Contract], [Count_Contract], [Count_Site], [Count_Presentation], [Value_NBV], [Value_ROU], [Value_Building], [Value_Land], [NBV_CY], [NBV_TotalAsset]

Key tables:
'CurMonData' = main site data with expenses and contracts
'Billing File' = cost allocation by PSL and facility
'Need Attention' = facilities needing review with addresses
'CurMonNBV' = NBV by architectural object
'REISPO' = space and occupancy data
'ZFAF' = asset financial data

Example queries:
Overview: EVALUATE ROW("Expired", [Count_Expired_Contract], "NBV", [Value_NBV], "ROU", [Value_ROU], "Contracts", [Count_Contract])
Billing by country: EVALUATE CALCULATETABLE(SUMMARIZECOLUMNS('Billing File'[Facility Name], 'Billing File'[PSL Name], "Cost", SUM('Billing File'[Allocated USD])), 'Billing File'[Country] = "Australia")
NBV by city: EVALUATE FILTER('Need Attention', 'Need Attention'[City] = "Comodoro Rivadavia")
Facilities by PSL: EVALUATE CALCULATETABLE(SUMMARIZECOLUMNS('Billing File'[Region], 'Billing File'[Country], 'Billing File'[Facility Name]), 'Billing File'[PSL Name] = "Cementing")
